Low-pressure gas adsorption measurements of CO2 (273, 283, 293 and 308 K) were performed on MicrotacBELsorp Max and MaxII gas adsorption analysers. Ultrahigh-purity (higher than 99.999%) CO2 in compressed gas cylinders was used throughout all experiments. Samples were degassed at 393 K for 12 h before measurement. CO2 adsorption isotherms of each COF were then fitted with virial model equations as follows:ln(p)=ln(N)+1T∑i=0mai×Ni+∑j=0nbj×Nj,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
