The isosteric heat of each COF was calculated from the virial fitting adsorption isotherms by using the Clausius–Clapeyron equation, in which Qst is the isosteric heat in J mol–1, T is the temperature in K, P is the pressure in kPa, and R is the gas constant (8.314 J K–1 mol–1):−Qst=RT2(∂lnP∂T)n\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
