The external quantum efficiencies (EQEs) for the photocatalytic H2 evolution were measured using monochromatic LED lamps (λ = 420, 490, 515 and 595 nm, respectively). For the experiments, the photocatalyst (2.5 mg) with Pt loading was suspended in an aqueous solution containing ascorbic acid (0.1 mol l−1). The light intensity was measured with a ThorLabs S120VC photodiode power sensor controlled by a ThorLabs PM100D Power and Energy Meter Console. The EQEs were estimated using the equation:EQE(%)=2×NumberofevolvedH2moleculesNumberofincidentphotons×100%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
